#!/usr/bin/env ssc
---
name: money-portable-v2
backends: [interpreter, v2]
---

# Portable Decimal / Money

The v2 VM must keep Decimal as an exact target-neutral value while executing
the real `std/money` helpers. The interpreter lane pins the established public
semantics; later compiled backends join this same fixture.

[money, plus, minorUnits, allocate, formatMoney](std/money.ssc)

```scalascript
println(formatMoney(plus(money("1.50", "USD"), money("2.25", "USD"))))
println(Decimal("1.0") == Decimal("1.00"))
println(Decimal("1.10") * Decimal("1.10"))
println(Decimal("10").divide(Decimal("3"), 4, RoundingMode.HALF_UP))
println(minorUnits(money("12.34", "USD")))
println(allocate(money("0.05", "USD"), List(1, 1, 1)).map(formatMoney))
```
